{"body": "```ruby\r\nrequire \"benchmark\"\r\n \r\nBenchmark.bm(7) do |x|\r\n  x.report(\"before:\")   do\r\n    (1..100000).each do\r\n      method = []\r\n      method << \"value = nil\"\r\n      method << \"halted = false\"\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n  x.report(\"after:\") do\r\n    (1..100000).each do\r\n      method =  [\"value = nil\", \"halted = false\"]\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n\r\n              user     system      total        real\r\nbefore:   0.090000   0.000000   0.090000 (  0.092787)\r\nafter:    0.080000   0.000000   0.080000 (  0.078116)\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou are right.  But, it seems like it also makes the code cleaner.  Not worth a huge debate over it tho.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/16860101", "created_at": "2013-04-23T14:08:33Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10318#issuecomment-16860101", "updated_at": "2013-04-23T14:09:37Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10318, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/siong1987", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/a955103782890eb2990826141b60d4ad?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa7471fdc77b3435276507cc8f2dc2569.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/received_events", "gravatar_id": "a955103782890eb2990826141b60d4ad", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "siong1987", "type": "User", "id": 5866, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/siong1987/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$